3 ways to add text to a file

1. vi
2. Redirect command output > or >> 
3. echo > or >> 

using "echo"
lets say we have a file named jerry
calvin@localhost:~$ echo "Hi i am in the file jerry" > jerry
so we can use "cat" to read inside the file
calvin@localhost:~$ cat jerry

Not: if we want to add another text in jerry this time we need to use double redirect sign >>
otherwise -if we use one redirect sign- the text we added will be deleted and write my new text
like single redirect sign overwrite 

using "> or >>"
lets say we have a file named keep.txt
So here i can write my result of something in keep.txt
calvin@localhost:~$ ls -ltr > keep.txt
this means write my ls -ltr result inside the file named keep.txt
like basically writing result in a file a choose 
calvin@localhost:~$ date >> jerry
it will write date inside jerry







